    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Still Needing, Still Feeding the Muse at 64'' by Allan Kozinn [June 3]:</p>
        <p>So the ''cute Beatle'' might seem even more frivolous in middle age. As a teenager I may have wept and screamed for Paul McCartney's music and his looks, but I respect him now for something more elevated.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Still Needing, Still Feeding the Muse at 64'' by Allan Kozinn [June 3]:</p>
        <p>So the ''cute Beatle'' might seem even more frivolous in middle age. As a teenager I may have wept and screamed for Paul McCartney's music and his looks, but I respect him now for something more elevated.</p>
        <p>What impresses about Mr. McCartney is that despite his share of life's pain or difficulties, his message is a lofty one: He says his song ''Gratitude'' is about ''me being grateful for the good stuff in my life, past and present.'' I find his optimism and his message an inspiring expression of grace.</p>
        <p>Gloria Averbuch  Upper Montclair, N.J.</p>
      </block>
